text:
(1) Coney Island, Dreamland Park:
Surf Ave., south side, between West 10th and 5th Streets, showing "The Tower" and lake which were demolished prior to 1917.

About 1908.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, looking north west from the beach. This property was converted into a public park prior to 1917, and all buildings in Dreamland were demolished.

About 1908.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Islands - Coney Island - Dreamland Park - [Dreamland Park tower.]

text:
Canoe Point, south of Surf Ave., east of West 5th Street, looking
towards Manhattan Beach.
About 1910.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Islands - Coney Island - Canoe Point.

text:
(1)
Surf Ave., north side, west of West 5th Street, showing in the foreground, the car barns of the Manhattan Transit R.R. Co., and beyond it the Brooklyn Edison Co's branch building. On the site of the car terminal, once stood the Vanderveer Concourse Hotel, which was opened on
December 10, 1878. It was demolished in 1902.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, looking eastward.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

West 5th Street, east side, between the "Boardwalk" (right) and Surf Ave., (left), showing the Municipal Building:-- a city bath-house, across clearing which is to be converted into the "Dreamland Parking Station"; city owned.

About 1927.
